# Copy the frames

_TEST_HELLO_

# Make a list. Keep monitoring until we have two files

_MAKE_A_LIST_ LIST=list.txt NFILE=2

# Form the difference.

_TWO_FRAME_DIFF_ 

=head1 NAME

TWO_FRAME_DIFF_STATS -- Take two frames and forms a difference.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This recipe waits until you have two frames in a group and then 
subtracts one from the other. The resulting frame is then available
for the user to do whatever statistical analysis he/she/it wants.

=head1 NOTES

None

=head1 OUTPUT DATA

=over 4

=item *

A FITS image with the difference of the two frames (first minus second)

=head1 CONFIGURABLE STEERING PARAMETERS

None

=head1 IMPLEMENTATION STATUS

=over 4

=item *

All processing is done with CIRDR routines.

=item *

Files are in standard Multi-extension FITS.

=back

=head1 REFERENCES

None

=head1 RELATED RECIPES

None

=head1 AUTHORS

Jim Lewis (CASU) (jrl@ast.cam.ac.uk)

=head1 COPYRIGHT

Copyright (C) 2004-2007 Cambridge Astronomical Survey Unit.
All Rights Reserved.

=cut
